description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you and experienced cardiac nurse with an interest in and experience of cardiac arrhythmias?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you want to join a large, friendly multi-disciplinary team at a regional specialist cardiac centre? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you want to work at an outstanding trust with nationally and internationally recognised strengths in cardiovascular research?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Advanced Nurse Practitioner for acute coronary syndrome (ACS) and cardiac rehabilitation (CR), you will be an integral member of the multidisciplinary team at the Bristol Heart Institute (BHI) and participate in the open access chest pain clinic services. This role will allow you utilise your skills of clinical expertise, leadership, education and management to ensure a seamless service for patients, carers and staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join a large team of Cardiac Surgical Advanced Nurse Practitioners, Surgical Care Practitioners, and Specialist Nurses in Acute Coronary Syndromes and cardiac rehabilitation, heart failure, arrhythmia, adult congenital heart and a team of research nurses. As a specialist nurse with an interest and experience of cardiac arrhythmias to be able to support the Hybrid Arrhythmia/ACS ANPs as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with the multidisciplinary team in hospital and the community to ensure a co-ordinated quality service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The BHI is the regional specialist cardiac centre for the South West and beyond. The BHI opened as a purpose built unit 2009. Since then, inpatients and outpatients have been seen for a full range of diagnostic and interventional treatments for heart conditions. It is now one of the leading centres for cardiovascular disease research in the UK.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why join us at UHBW? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Because we are passionate about supporting our staff and clinical teams, so that we can achieve our common goal of delivering outstanding patient care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Because we can offer job security in these uncertain times within an organisation that is dedicated to the wellbeing of its staff. We understand that we work to live (not live to work) and support flexible and part-time working patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Because we are one of a handful of health trusts to have achieved a CQC rating of “Outstanding” for a second time second time in succession.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Because we are located in the heart of the vibrant City of Bristol, and the gateway to the glorious South West.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jacqueline Fear - Matron, Bristol Heart Institute&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jacqueline.Fear@uhbw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
